caption: What a fantastic little French spot. We had the quiche Parisienne and strawberry crepe. The crepe was delicious, but the true star is the quiche. Absolutely the best quiche I’ve had in years. And a generous portion as well. Their back patio is perfect and adorable. They serve Big Shoulders coffee, which I love.
Outstanding food! You taste the superior quality within the first bite. It's really really excellent quality french food. Highly recommended

Wonderful Quiche Provençale. They offer many vegetarian options and the staff is very friendly. I plan to stop by again to try a croissant and a few of their tarts. The owner mentioned that they have outdoor seating when its warm. Highly recommend this beautiful café.

I find it challenging to find nice places to get a tasty quick bite with coffee plus a good study environment... but I found it! They have plenty of vegetarian options and dairy free milk and the quiche is delicious. Staff was friendly and warm and the inside seating was socially distanced and not packed! Such a great find in my Lincoln park area, especially during COVID. Will be a regular here for certain!
Wonderful addition to the neighborhood!! Delicious crusty French bread, quiches & more. Thank you for delivering!
Phenominal place. Best quiche I have ever tried. Crepes with strawberries were delicious. Definitely one of the best breakfast places in Chicago!
Great food, especially sandwiches, which bring back travel memories.
Absolutely delicious! We loved the authentic French cuisine. Highly recommend!

After living in France for nearly 7 years I can tell you I miss my (nearly daily) boulangerie/pâtisserie visits so I am very pleased to have discovered French Quiche.  Everything is so fresh and delicious. My favorites so far have been the orzo salad and the pan Bagnat. I also have to mention as it is the most important thing to me for a great French sandwich, the bread is spot on.  Thank you for a couple delicious meals and lovely service, à bientôt !
We’ve had soup, quiche, sandwiches and Chef’s “Kings cake” - YUM!  Everything is tasty.  Great local find.
Friendly fresh and delicious. Wonderful selection. Lovey atmosphere.

I wish this place was good because I would love nothing more than to support a cute French cafe down the street from my apartment. Unfortunately, I cannot support the food here that is just heated up as you order it, including the crepes which are not made fresh to order. The crepe was cold and left much to be desired. There are many crepe places in Chicago worth supporting, unfortunately, this is not one of them. After asking one of the employees about the cold crepe, they were less than interested in hearing the critique which led me to the review. If I knew things were being worked out and they were interested in feedback, I would’ve left it at that- but the attitude here is not necessary.

Simply perfection! One of the best locations in Chicago to grab an excellent breakfast/lunch. Selections of freshly made foods make it difficult to choose. I however choose a slice of quiche and an almond croissant.  The quiche is amazingly creamy and fluffy.  The first bite was the wow moment, so delicious. Make sure this is your next destination.

We were excited to try this place out after seeing it open up down the street from our house.. Unfortunately, it was a horrible experience. We love crepes and have had them in numerous European countries and repeatedly at local Chicago restaurants. We have never had crepes like this. The first crepe we ordered was stuffed whip cream and was cold to the touch. I’ve never had a crepe with whip cream inside so we decided to order a 2nd one and say no whip cream: This time, I saw them pull out a stack of pre-made crepes from a refrigerator and stick one for a few seconds in a countertop oven and then smear some Nutella inside of it.  It was also cold and as we told the man who made it about this he said a) it’s supposed to be served cold b) they don’t have time to make the crepes at the time of ordering and c) that next time when we order after they make it we should tell them to pop it in the microwave . It was really an embarrassment and a sorry excuse for a small French patisserie. I will not be going back as there are way better places in the neighborhood to support. The man who we gave the critique wasn’t interested in hearing it.
Wonderful quiche, soup and crepes to die for!  What a nice addition to the neighborhood!
Very fresh ingredients, especially their bread!  Flavors were excellent. Highly recommend trying this place.
What an awesome add to the neighborhood! A great place to get coffee and breakfast to go. The staff is really friendly! Definitely visit and try it out.
Love the decor and the orzo salad. Will return!
Nice place and excellent food

Magnifique! This is a new Lincoln Park gem. We were welcomed in by a warm and friendly staff. The interior is gorgeous with stunning tile floors, rustic wrought iron decor, cozy indoor seating areas and a lovely outdoor patio.  Can't wait til we can sit inside and out there. In the meantime, check out their carry-out. Great croissants, sandwiches, salads, soups and of course..quiche!

How wonderful to have a new, exciting French Quarters-style cafe in Lincoln Park!  From quiches, to soups, sandwiches and salads, it’s all delicious!  You can get it all to go, too! Uniquely charming indoors and a lovely private courtyard in the rear. Well done FQ!

I've only had the Quiche Lorraine, the Quiche Provençale, and the soupe du jour which was tomato soup and it was all fantastic. My favorite was the Quiche Lorraine but I would certainly order everything again. The quiches are definitely best ate fresh though they still travel well. The tomato soup was not too creamy which I was a fan of. Will definitely be returning!

I went the day after they opened. The food was beautiful AND delicious.  They have 4 salads, 4 flatbreads, 4 sandwiches, 4 quiches, and 4 desserts from which to choose. They also serve Big Shoulders coffee and other coffee/tea drinks, as well as croissants, breads, and more.  It took a long time to narrow down my first selection. I got the Parisienne Quiche and the Mediterranean salad (which I put on a bed of spring lettuce when I got home). The salad was delicately, but perfectly seasoned; the quiche was fluffy and dense with flavor.  The chef/owner (who is also the chef of Chez Moi down the block) was there to greet everyone and the staff was friendly and competent.  When the world is more "normal," I'd love to linger longer; but in the mean time, it's great for delicious takeout and coffee. Overall, prices are reasonable, quality is high, and worth checking out.
Absolutely amazing quiches!!!
